[3] Brazil (Guaruja, Sao Paulo)
Date: Sat 13 Mar 2010
Source: Diario da Manha, O Estado de S Paulo report [in Portuguese,
trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://site.dm.com.br/noticias/cidades/com-962-casos-de-dengue-guaruja-decreta-epidemia>


The Guaruja government yesterday [12 Mar 2010] declared a dengue
epidemic in this coastal Sao Paulo municipality, which registered 962
cases of the disease, with 7 deaths. Another 996 people await the
results of [laboratory] tests from the Instituto Adolfo Lutz. The
Secretariat of Health bulleting issued on 27 Feb [2010] indicated
that there were 7594 reports of the disease in the state since the
beginning of year [2010].

The neighborhood with the greatest dengue incidence is Pae Cara,
located in the Vicente de Carvalho district. In an attempt to
eliminate the mosquito vector of the disease [virus], trucks with
[insecticide] foggers were sent to the region. Jardim Enseada also
has had an increase in the number of infected individuals, with 100
confirmed cases.

In order to accelerate medical attention, the municipality decided to
adopt a measure similar to that of Praia Grande municipality.
Starting today [13 Mar 2010], people will have access to tents
installed in front of emergency units to carry out diagnoses. In
addition to this, nurses and nursing technicians have emergency
contracts to work in medical posts in bus stations, where people come
to sit on the floor waiting for [medical] care.

--
