[4] Brazil (Ribeirao Preto, Sao Paulo)
Date: Thu 11 Mar 2010
Source: Ribeirao Preto Online [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.ribeiraopretoonline.com.br/saude/epidemia-de-dengue-ja-e-considerada-a-pior-dos-ultimos-dez-anos-em-ribeirao/34522>


The Secretariat of Health of Ribeirao Preto this Wednesday (10 Mar
2010]), reported in an announcement the current confirmed [number of]
dengue cases in the city. According to that information, 3074
Ribeirao Preto residents have now been infected with this disease and
another 3399 are considered suspected [cases]. On average 44.5
[cases] are registered daily.

The fight against proliferation of the mosquito _Aedes aegypti_,
vector of the disease [virus], continues. Visits to houses, some
facilitated by court order, inspections of commercial points, fogging
services, campaigns for public awareness, task forces [are] measures
which are intensified each day in the fight against the disease.
According to SMS [municipal health secretariat], the epidemic [that
the city is] living through this year [2010] is the worst of the 9
registered in the city since 1990.

--
