[5] Brazil (Rio Grande do Sul)
Date: Sat 13 Mar 2010
Source: Bahia Noticias [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.bahianoticias.com.br/noticias/noticia/2010/03/13/59188,rs-mais-de-2-mil-casos-de-dengue-em-20-dias.html>


Since the dengue outbreak was announced on 22 Feb [2010], a total of
2052 dengue cases have been recorded in Rio Grande do Sul. According
to the state Secretariat of Health, the city most affected is Ijui,
in the northwest part of the state, with 1721 recorded [cases]. The
other registered [cases] are distributed in 55 municipalities in the
same region. The head of the office, Osmar Terra, admitted to G1 that
the number of infected individuals could reach 5000 in coming days,
but stated that the trend is to decline in a month, because of the
fall in temperature.

--
