[6] Brazil (Mato Grosso do Sul)
Date: Fri 12 Mar 2010
Source: Estado.com.br [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.estadao.com.br/noticias/geral,situacao-da-dengue-em-ms-e-alarmante-diz-governo,523343,0.htm>


More than half of the 78 municipalities in Mato Grosso do Sul failed
to send the data sheets for the dengue situation since last week
[week of 1 Mar 2010]. Despite this failure, which represents 58
percent less information, the epidemiological bulletin released today
[12 Mar 2010] by the state Secretariat of Health shows alarming data.
Up to the last day, 6 [Mar 2010], a total of 11 [dengue] deaths were
registered this year [2010] in Mato Grosso do Sul, with 32 225
reported [dengue] cases.

"The epidemic of the disease is considered alarming in 8
municipalities," stated the information [bulletin]. With 20 250
reported [cases], Campo Grande has an incidence of 2682 cases per 100
000 population, among other cities with "a very high" index, such as
Jardim with 1299 cases, Angelica with 2518, Corguinho with 1875,
Ivinhema with 2122, Nioaque with 2198, Pedro Gomes with 1942, and Rio
Brilhante with 3369 cases per 100 000 population.

[Byline: Joao Naves de Oliveira]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

