[7] Argentina (north)
Date: Sat 13 Mar 2010
Source: La Manana [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.lmcordoba.com.ar/nota.php?ni=6301>


There are 672 confirmed dengue cases in the country. To this number,
2 confirmed cases in Cordoba must be added -- 2 people who traveled
to Venezuela and Brazil, where they contracted the virus [infection].
The majority of the [locally acquired] cases occurred in Misiones and
Chaco [provinces], where there is an outbreak with 536 and 103
patients, respectively.

Since December 2009 until the present, the National Reference
Laboratory (INEVH) "Julio I Maiztegui", has confirmed the circulation
of dengue [virus] serotype 1 (DEN-1) in Argentina. A total of 672
dengue illnesses have been recorded in the country since 1 Jan 2010
up to today. In Misiones [province] there is an outbreak with a total
of 536 cases detected in 2010. In Chaco [province] 103 dengue
patients have been recorded. Meanwhile, in Buenos Aires, Santa Fe,
Entre Rios and Salta provinces, between 2-3 cases of patients with
this disease have been confirmed.

Data provided by the national Ministry of Health do not include the 2
confirmed cases in Cordoba, since they include [dengue] patients
reported from 1 Jan-9 Mar [2010]. The minister of health, Oscar
Gonzalez, made the formal announcement last [Thu 11 Mar 2010].

It is worth noting that in the outbreak areas response activities are
continuing: strengthening of service networks, their reorganization
such as the actions that the technical teams are in charge of, and
health personnel of the affected municipalities, the provinces and
the national Ministry of Health. The control actions include trash
cleanup, barriers around foci [of virus transmission] -- fumigation
around the blocks adjoining houses of infected people -- and search
for febrile patients with dengue symptoms.

--
